div1.p:
Q. Had any body command of the party - A. Yes;
James West
to the left, and M. Lawrence to the right; Beer was with West, I believe, I saw them going down, and think he went to the left; he was armed with a pistol, when I saw him going down. I was on the right division; I saw Williams, he was armed with a pistol, and I think he was on the left division. Homans was armed with a pistol, I believe he was on the left. J. Richardson was armed, and I think had a short gun, and the other a longer, but I am not certain; I know one of them had a short gun, and the other a long gun - I am certain both were armed.
